Reuters French Advertising & Media Digest - May 20 . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - FAM - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - REUTERS FRENCH ADVERTISING & MEDIA DIGEST - - - - - - - - - - - - May 20 , 1997 - - - - - - - - - - - - News from Reuters and the French press on Advertising , Marketing , Media , the Internet and Brand - name Products . * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ADVERTISING & MARKETING : PARIS - Publicis says its turnover rose six percent to 5 . 18 billion francs ( $ 905 . 4 million ) in the first quarter of 1997 , largely due to expansion abroad . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * PARIS - RMC and Sud Communication are putting together the fine details of the merger . They still have to negotiate agreements for their advertising space units . ( La Tribune ) * * * * * * * * * LONDON - Excite Inc says it launches European editions of its Internet search engines which will extend the reach of the Excite network , increase functionality and meet specific advertising requirements . Local products are launched in Britain , France , Germany and Sweden . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * PARIS - Jacqueline Aglietta , chairman of French audience measurement body Mediametrie , defends TV viewing figures published by Mediametrie . Its figures have recently come under fire in a debate on audience numbers which is now widening to include the content of French TV programmes . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * MEDIA & THE INTERNET : PARIS - Turnover at publisher Filipacchi Medias rose to 375 . 1 million francs in the first quarter from 373 . 0 million in 1996 ' s first three months , the company says . Magazine and advertising turnover fell in the period . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * PARIS - Newly - launched French weekly news magazine Marianne ' s first few issues put it above breakeven , but its competitors have not so far suffered from its arrival . ( La Tribune ) . * * * * * * * * * PARIS - French film industry watcher Centre National de la Cinematographie ' s most recent study says film production has shown a sharp recovery in Britain , Germany and Spain . ( Les Echos ) * * * * * * * * * CANNES - Cannes festival - goers wonder aloud why the film festival ' s 50th edition was made up of so many uninspiring films reeking of violence and evil . The jury rescued the jamboree with awards for a quirky Japanese film , " The Eel " by Shohei Imamura , and by flagging its support for two directors who have tussled with censors . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * BRAND NAME PRODUCTS & MARKETS : PARIS - Dairy farmers blocked deliveries to hypermarkets in various parts of France in a protest against falling milk prices , unions say . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * LONDON - French authorities may question the planned merger between British drinks giants Guinness and Grand Metropolitan , the Independent newspaper says . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * PARIS - French drinks brand Orangina , a unit of Pernod Ricard , has begun delivering its fizzy orange drink in plastic screw - top bottles in France in a bid to target younger consumers , an Orangina spokeswoman says . ( Reuter ) * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * Paris Editorial , Sue LandauTel 33 1 42 21 53 33Fax 33 1 42 36 10 72 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * For further information and news , see Reuters Advertising & Media Briefing . And visit us on the Internet at http : / / www . Bizinfo . reuters . com * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ( $ = 5 . 721 French Francs ) 
